  meanings
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "A fact or statement used to support a proposition; a reason."
        entry
          definition "A verbal dispute; a quarrel."
        entry
          definition "A process of reasoning."
        entry
          definition "A series of propositions organized so that the final proposition is a conclusion which is intended to follow logically from the preceding propositions, which function as premises."
        entry
          definition "The independent variable of a function."
        entry
          definition "The phase of a complex number."
        entry
          definition "A value, or reference to a value, passed to a function."
          example "Parameters are like labeled fillable blanks used to define a function whereas arguments are passed to a function when calling it, filling in those blanks."
        entry
          definition "A parameter at a function call; an actual parameter, as opposed to a formal parameter."
        entry
          definition "Any of the phrases that bears a syntactic connection to the verb of a clause."
        entry
          definition "The quantity on which another quantity in a table depends."
          example "The altitude is the argument of the refraction."
        entry
          definition "The subject matter of a discourse, writing, or artistic representation; theme or topic; also, an abstract or summary, as of the contents of a book, chapter, poem."
        entry
          definition "Matter for question; business in hand."
      partOfSpeech noun
      synonyms ("actual argument" "passed parameter")
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "(NNES) To put forward as an argument; to argue."
      partOfSpeech verb
  phonetic "/ˈɑːɡjʊmənt/"
